  margin-top: 1rem;
}

{
  padding: 0;
}
```
This is a wrong behaviour, as rules order is modified, margin-top for p will be 1rem instead of 0.

If we replace rem with px:
```
p {
  margin-top: 1px;
}

{
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
}

p {
  margin: 0;
} 
```
it compiles to:
```
*, p {
  margin: 0;
}

{
  padding: 0;
}
```
I hope this will help to find a fix.
